Thursday afternoon, if that

00:13:04.780 --> 00:13:08.160
works for you. We're hoping
to learn how to simmer a fish.

00:13:08.250 --> 00:13:09.710
[TSUKI]
That sounds wonderful, sweetie.

00:13:09.790 --> 00:13:11.290
I'll get the ingredients.

00:13:11.370 --> 00:13:14.500
[UZAKI] Yay, thanks Mom. I'll
make sure it's on the calendar.

00:13:14.590 --> 00:13:16.050
Cooking lessons, eh?

00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:18.510
Is this the same friend who made
all that udon a while back?

00:13:18.590 --> 00:13:19.720
That was them, all right.

00:13:19.800 --> 00:13:21.260
I suppose when you're
living on your own,

00:13:21.340 --> 00:13:23.430
it can inspire you to
learn some cooking skills.

00:13:23.510 --> 00:13:26.390
But I've never seen a new chef
taking food this seriously.

00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:29.680
Really now? Such determination!
I can get behind that.

00:13:29.770 --> 00:13:32.480
I bet this girl will make
a great wife one day.

00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:35.150
Actually, my friend's a dude.

00:13:35.230 --> 00:13:37.320
And send text.

00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:41.910
[FUJIO]
Huh, my bad. I stand corrected.

00:13:41.990 --> 00:13:44.240
It's a shame I won't
get to meet this guy.

00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:45.820
Know what, I think
I'll just go ahead

00:13:45.910 --> 00:13:47.540
and take the day off
so I can join you.

00:13:47.620 --> 00:13:49.500
What are you talking
about Fujio, you can't.

00:13:49.580 --> 00:13:51.000
Didn't we agree
you'd save your PTO?

00:13:51.080 --> 00:13:53.960
[laughing]

